## 10. Super-Upgrade Roadmap

### 🎯 Level 1: Intelligent Agent (Current → Next)

- [x] Multi-iterative reasoning loop
- [x] Self-evolution (tool creation)
- [x] Sub-agent delegation
- [ ] **Context Intelligence** — weighted, importance-scored context
- [ ] **Self-Correction** — structured error recovery
- [ ] **Adaptive Tools** — request-aware tool filtering
- [ ] **Performance Telemetry** — real-time metrics

### 🎯 Level 2: Autonomous Agent

- [ ] **Long-Term Memory** — persistent cross-session knowledge
- [ ] **Context Summarization** — LLM-compressed history
- [ ] **Codebase Semantic Index** — function/class/variable index
- [ ] **Predictive Tool Use** — predict likely next tool based on history
- [ ] **Multi-Agent Shared Memory** — sub-agents share findings

### 🎯 Level 3: Self-Evolving Platform

- [ ] **Plugin Architecture** — load external tool packages
- [ ] **Agent State Machine** — pause/resume/checkpoint
- [ ] **Streaming Responses** — progressive output rendering
- [ ] **Auto-Project Understanding** — automatic README/architecture analysis on first load
- [ ] **Behavioral Learning** — track which tools succeed for which patterns

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Implementation Principle:** Every enhancement should be **incremental** and **backward-compatible**. New modules should be opt-in via constructor injection, not forced refactoring. The existing agentic loop must continue to work unchanged while new capabilities are layered on top.

---

> **End of Architectural Analysis**  
> This blueprint provides a clear path from FLASH AI v2.5's current state to a **world-class autonomous AI agent platform**, while respecting the Ring language ecosystem and the project's modular design philosophy.
